		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2014"></a><br><code>sle2014/paper09</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014</a> paper:</span><br><i>AIOCJ: A Choreographic Framework for Safe Adaptive Distributed Applications</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MilaDallaPreda.html">Mila Dalla Preda</a>, <a href="../profile/SaverioGiallorenzo.html">Saverio Giallorenzo</a>, <a href="../profile/IvanLanese.html">Ivan Lanese</a>, <a href="../profile/JacopoMauro.html">Jacopo Mauro</a>, <a href="../profile/MaurizioGabbrielli.html">Maurizio Gabbrielli</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_9">10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_9</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> It introduces a domain-specific choreographic language for specifying distributed interaction patterns.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagL">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> Adaptation is performed at runtime via rules that update executing distributed applications.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagL">T1C: Behavioural Semantics</span></a><ul><li> The framework emphasizes safe executable behavior of distributed choreographies under adaptation.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It includes compilation/generation aspects from global choreographies to executable distributed code.
</li></ul></li></ul>
